MATCH_TOOL: Bash
MATCH_PATTERN: po-logs-(staging|production)
ADVISORY: |
  Axiom has two services in po-logs-*: `game-server-*` and `pecking-order-lobby-*`.
  Pick the right one before querying.

  For game-state investigations (voting, cartridges, transitions):
    - Target `game-server-*`, which uses internal IDs `game-{timestamp}-{random}`.
    - Invite codes (e.g., M48TJ8) appear in lobby logs, not game-server logs.
    - Resolve invite code → internal game ID first via lobby logs, then query game-server.

  For invite/join funnel investigations (who tapped what, bounce rates):
    - Target `pecking-order-lobby-*` directly. Lobby logs are HTTP access logs:
      `GET /join/CODE`, `POST /login?next=...`, `/invite/TOKEN`, etc.
    - Lobby logs do NOT contain app-level state. Cross-reference D1 (`InviteTokens`,
      `Invites`, `GameSessions`) for token-used status, slot acceptance, etc.
    - D1 queries: `npx wrangler d1 execute pecking-order-lobby-db-{env} --env {env}
      --remote --command "SQL" --json`.
